{
  "decision_conditions": [
    "Condition : 1 - The proposal fails to meet the minimum original floor area required to be eligible for conversion to a HMO and is not located a suitable location for a HMO, due to the distance to the town centre facilities and insufficient access to public transport. The proposal is therefore unacceptable in principle, contrary to Local Plan Policy SC10 and the Houses in Multiple Occupation SPG",
    "Condition : 2 - The applicant has failed to demonstrate that the proposal would not result in an unacceptable highways impact. The proposed development is therefore contrary to Local Plan Policy EC2, London Plan Policy T5 and the LBH Residential Crossovers and Off-Street Parking Policy (2016)",
    "Reason : 1 - The proposal fails to meet the minimum original floor area required to be eligible for conversion to a HMO and is not located a suitable location for a HMO, due to the distance to the town centre facilities and insufficient access to public transport. The proposal is therefore unacceptable in principle, contrary to Local Plan Policy SC10 and the Houses in Multiple Occupation SPG",
    "Reason : 2 - The applicant has failed to demonstrate that the proposal would not result in an unacceptable highways impact to the detriment of highway and pedestrian safety together with the living conditions of the neighbouring occupiers. The proposed development is therefore contrary to Local Plan Policy EC2, London Plan Policy T5 and the LBH Residential Crossovers and Off-Street Parking Policy (2016). "
